			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>About Us</strong></p>
<p>
Retention Science team consists of serial entrepreneurs from Caltech, UC Berkeley, UCLA, USC &amp; Yale. Our team has received awards like Ernst &amp; Young Entrepreneur of the Year and been named an &ldquo;Innovation Agent&rdquo; by Fast Company. Retention Science has been named a Top 10 Big Data Startup of the Year as well as a Top 10 Software Company in Southern California by SocalTech. We&rsquo;ve been featured in Forbes, TechCrunch, Bloomberg, Fox News, Reuters, etc.</p>
<p>
Retention Science is building the first &ldquo;Retention Automation Platform&rdquo; &ndash; a B2B enterprise software to help e-Commerce increase existing customer spending. We employ cutting-edge predictive technology and big data analytics to help e-Commerce businesses understand customer behaviors and maximize customer retention. Our software-as-a-service profiling engine uses machine learning techniques and statistical models to analyze purchasing trends based on massive demographic, social, and behavioral data sets. We use these data points to automatically generate retention strategies for each individual customer.</p>
<p>
The intern will have direct exposure to all aspects of our business and you will learn A LOT.</p>
<p>
Retention Science is based in sunny Santa Monica. For more info, please visit: http://www.retentionscience.com/</p>
<p>
<strong>Job Description</strong></p>
<p>
We are looking for a true go-getter and scrappy hustler. We are looking for an intern to support our enterprise sales team and is interested in selling marketing technology, data analytics solutions or B2B software.<br />
Responsibilities<br />
&bull; Develop, implement, maintain, and/or improve sales techniques<br />
&bull; Develop and implement both short-term and long-term strategic sales initiatives<br />
&bull; Develop and maintain a strong understanding of market trends and opportunities<br />
&bull; Monitor sales initiatives to meet key milestones</p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong></p>
<p>
&bull; Exceptional communication skills, both written and verbal<br />
&bull; Understanding of complex sales cycles with experience implementing internal processes to improve efficiency<br />
&bull; Experience or willingness to learn and be proficient with SFA tools, such as salesforce.com</p>
